<Folder><name>Waypoints</name><Placemark><name>Kuranda</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>145.638300,-16.820700,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Mareeba</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>145.422500,-17.001100,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Atherton</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>145.477500,-17.268300,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Yungaburra / Curtain Fig</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>145.580300,-17.269700,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Lake Eacham</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>145.630600,-17.279200,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Lake Barrine</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>145.639400,-17.240000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Millaa Millaa</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>145.617200,-17.502800,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Millaa Millaa Falls</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>145.627500,-17.509700,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Innisfail</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>146.026900,-17.524700,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Babinda Boulders</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>145.921700,-17.343300,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Gordonvale</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>145.778300,-17.032200,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark></Folder>
<Folder><name>Scenic Points</name><Placemark><name>Kuranda</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Rainforest village reached by either the 1891 Kuranda Scenic Railway (15 tunnels through gorge country) or the Skyrail cable car gliding above the canopy. Markets daily.]]></description><Point><coordinates>145.638300,-16.820700,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Mareeba — coffee and mango country</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Drier rainshadow side of the range — Australia's coffee belt and most of its mango exports. Skybury and Jaques estates do tours; Granite Gorge nearby is a wild rock-wallaby colony.]]></description><Point><coordinates>145.422500,-17.001100,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Curtain Fig Tree</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[500-year-old strangler fig whose host tree fell at an angle, leaving the fig's aerial roots as a 15 m vertical curtain to the forest floor. Boardwalk loop (5 minutes).]]></description><Point><coordinates>145.580300,-17.269700,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Lake Eacham</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Crater lake in dense rainforest — 65 m deep, formed by a phreatic eruption ~9,000 years ago. Swimming, picnic ground, 3 km loop walk. Snake-necked turtles in the shallows.]]></description><Point><coordinates>145.630600,-17.279200,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Millaa Millaa Falls</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[18 m horsetail falls dropping into a green pool — the most-photographed waterfall in Australia. The hair-flick photograph belongs to a thousand backpackers. Continue the 16 km loop to Zillie and Ellinjaa Falls.]]></description><Point><coordinates>145.627500,-17.509700,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Babinda Boulders</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Granite-bouldered swimming hole (warning: drowning blackspot — swim only the upper Devil's Pool only at posted depths). The Yidinji legend behind the place is darker than the brochure version.]]></description><Point><coordinates>145.921700,-17.343300,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark></Folder>
</Document></kml>
